DOHA, QATAR, January 16, 2023/APO Group/ --
                                                        
                            The State of Qatar expresses its strong condemnation and denunciation of the bombing that targeted a church in North Kivu province in Eastern Democratic Republic of Congo, which resulted in deaths and injuries.
                                The Ministry also expresses the condolences of the State of Qatar to the families of the victims
                            



The Ministry of Foreign Affairs reiterates Qatarâ€™s firm position on rejecting violence and terrorism, regardless of motives and reasons. It also stresses its total rejection targeting places of worship and intimidating safe civilians.

The Ministry also expresses the condolences of the State of Qatar to the families of the victims and to the government and people of Congo, wishing the injured a speedy recovery.